==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Opacity
<hw>O*pac"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>opacitas</ets>: cf. F. opacit⟦eacute⟧.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state of being opaque; the quality of a body which renders it impervious
to the rays of light; want of transparency; opaqueness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Obscurity; want of clearness.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opacous</ent>⟦br⟧
